00:42:00.420 --> 00:42:02.860
and that plus some court decisions

00:42:02.860 --> 00:42:06.510
generated the intelligent
design movement, so, you know,

00:42:06.510 --> 00:42:09.020
if it's not one damn thing,
it's another. (laughs)

00:42:09.020 --> 00:42:12.830
- You also, in your book,
have an interesting discussion

00:42:12.830 --> 00:42:16.530
of essentially myth, and of the notion,

00:42:16.530 --> 00:42:19.500
and myth being the ideas that are central

00:42:19.500 --> 00:42:24.500
to a society or a nation, and in a way,

00:42:25.310 --> 00:42:30.310
some of the myths come
from the way people live,

00:42:30.700 --> 00:42:32.970
the social experience of their lives,

00:42:32.970 --> 00:42:35.220
and you pointed out that the school,

00:42:35.220 --> 00:42:40.220
the history of the schools being
a decentralized enterprise,

00:42:40.500 --> 00:42:42.980
you talked about, as are the churches.

00:42:42.980 --> 00:42:45.693
And so you got local control,

00:42:48.210 --> 00:42:51.890
which means that all the battles

00:42:51.890 --> 00:42:55.050
are often in a decentralized area,

00:42:55.050 --> 00:42:59.793
as you discussed in your
first awakening to this.

00:43:01.570 --> 00:43:04.230
It seems, so this is what
I wanna to pose to you,

00:43:04.230 --> 00:43:09.230
which is the progressive
agenda really often comes

00:43:09.350 --> 00:43:12.810
from a center at the national level,

00:43:12.810 --> 00:43:17.810
whereas then the fight
emerges with the local level,

00:43:19.370 --> 00:43:24.370
which embraces some of the non-scientific

00:43:27.809 --> 00:43:29.420
ways of looking at things.

00:43:29.420 --> 00:43:32.150
Talk a little about that, is that unfair?

00:43:32.150 --> 00:43:34.163
- Well, (sighs)

00:43:35.530 --> 00:43:36.440
it's a push me pull you kinda thing,

00:43:36.440 --> 00:43:38.790
yeah.
- Yeah, yeah.

00:43:38.790 --> 00:43:42.230
- Education is highly decentralized.

00:43:42.230 --> 00:43:44.330
Decisions about what gets taught,

00:43:44.330 --> 00:43:46.120
who's gonna teach, how
much you're gonna pay,

00:43:46.120 --> 00:43:48.190
those are all local decisions.

00:43:48.190 --> 00:43:51.230
To some degree in the last 20 years,

00:43:51.230 --> 00:43:53.690
the focus has shifted a
little bit more to the state

00:43:53.690 --> 00:43:55.490
partly for funding reasons.

00:43:55.490 --> 00:43:58.530
If the state is gonna give
money to the local districts,

00:43:58.530 --> 00:44:00.280
they can tie strings to it

00:44:00.280 --> 00:44:05.015
so there may be some curricular pressures

00:44:05.015 --> 00:44:06.760
on local districts, but really,

00:44:06.760 --> 00:44:09.550
a local district can decide
to thumb its nose at the state

00:44:09.550 --> 00:44:11.273
and teach any damn thing it wants,

00:44:12.860 --> 00:44:15.630
within constitutional (laughs) reason.

00:44:15.630 --> 00:44:17.980
You can't teach the violent
overthrow of the government.

00:44:17.980 --> 00:44:20.360
That's treason, so they're
not gonna teach that.

00:44:20.360 --> 00:44:23.400
But the decentralization
is really important

00:44:23.400 --> 00:44:28.400
in American education, and so as a result,

00:44:28.820 --> 00:44:31.930
when evolution creeps
back into the textbooks

00:44:31.930 --> 00:44:36.830
and people on the local level
notice, this tends to support

00:44:36.830 --> 00:44:39.643
national anti-evolutionist organizations.

00:44:41.300 --> 00:44:44.320
The Institute for Creation Research

00:44:44.320 --> 00:44:46.770
and later Answers in
Genesis and a whole raft

00:44:46.770 --> 00:44:49.760
of small anti-evolutionist organizations

00:44:49.760 --> 00:44:51.960
have sprung up at different times.

00:44:51.960 --> 00:44:55.433
The IC are being the most
important in terms of my work,

00:44:56.300 --> 00:45:00.460
and they are very influential

00:45:00.460 --> 00:45:03.630
'cause they're sort of
our evil twin. (laughs)

00:45:03.630 --> 00:45:05.590
Somebody's gonna quote
me on that, I know it,

00:45:05.590 --> 00:45:08.840
but they provide information
for their grassroots people

00:45:08.840 --> 00:45:11.270
just like NCSE provides information

00:45:11.270 --> 00:45:14.230
for grassroots people on
our side of this issue

00:45:14.230 --> 00:45:16.700
to better persuade decision-makers

00:45:16.700 --> 00:45:18.470
at the local and state level.
- We can't say they're evil.

00:45:18.470 --> 00:45:19.490
- No, yeah.
- They're just the opposite

00:45:19.490 --> 00:45:22.440
side, yeah, okay, we'll just, yeah, yeah.

00:45:22.440 --> 00:45:24.540
- It's a joke about the evil twin

00:45:24.540 --> 00:45:26.990
'cause that's a cultural motif, but yeah.

00:45:26.990 --> 00:45:28.800
But it's like the black and the white,

00:45:28.800 --> 00:45:31.530
it's like the yin and yang.

00:45:31.530 --> 00:45:35.460
The national organizations
provide information

00:45:35.460 --> 00:45:37.820
to the grassroots but
if it doesn't get done

00:45:37.820 --> 00:45:39.770
at the grassroots, it doesn't get done.

00:45:42.160 --> 00:45:44.690
People always ask me, oh,
with the new administration,

00:45:44.690 --> 00:45:46.680
or now that that administration is gone,

00:45:46.680 --> 00:45:48.660
it's gonna be easier,
it's gonna be harder.

00:45:48.660 --> 00:45:52.010
The federal government has hardly anything

00:45:52.010 --> 00:45:53.740
to do with curriculum,

00:45:53.740 --> 00:45:56.860
and whether evolution is taught
or not is a curricular issue

00:45:56.860 --> 00:46:01.110
and curriculum is determined
at the state and local level,

00:46:01.110 --> 00:46:04.060
so regardless of what somebody

00:46:04.060 --> 00:46:08.160
in a given administration
believes about creationism,

00:46:08.160 --> 00:46:10.460
they're not gonna be able
to do a heck of a lot

00:46:10.460 --> 00:46:14.120
to see that when the
classroom door gets shut

00:46:14.120 --> 00:46:15.530
in Mrs. Brown's classroom,

00:46:15.530 --> 00:46:18.130
she's gonna pull out the
creation science materials.

00:46:18.980 --> 00:46:23.090
There also has been a legal
history of the battles

00:46:23.090 --> 00:46:25.743
between evolution and anti-evolution for,

00:46:27.180 --> 00:46:29.743
well, let's see now, for almost 100 years.

00:46:31.310 --> 00:46:34.470
That is very relevant to this
whole controversy as well.

00:46:34.470 --> 00:46:37.820
But just in terms of
the national grassroots,

00:46:37.820 --> 00:46:41.343
decentralization, versus local control,

00:46:42.770 --> 00:46:44.430
it's a combination of factors.

00:46:44.430 --> 00:46:49.170
But the NCSE would not have
been able to accomplish

00:46:49.170 --> 00:46:52.980
as much as it's accomplished
over the years of our existence

00:46:52.980 --> 00:46:55.630
if it hadn't been for people
at the grassroots willing

00:46:55.630 --> 00:46:58.950
to take the time and spend the energy

00:46:58.950 --> 00:47:02.660
and tremendous amount of
effort in trying to see

00:47:02.660 --> 00:47:05.090
that good science gets
taught in their schools.

00:47:05.090 --> 00:47:06.480
- As we see in the world today,

00:47:06.480 --> 00:47:10.080
let's talk about today
and we see a movement

00:47:10.080 --> 00:47:15.080
across the globe toward
authoritarianism in various degrees.

00:47:16.470 --> 00:47:20.210
Some might even speculate
about that movement here

00:47:20.210 --> 00:47:21.290
in the United States.

00:47:21.290 --> 00:47:26.247
And authoritarian demagogic leaders

00:47:27.370 --> 00:47:30.170
basically often built their

00:47:32.660 --> 00:47:37.660
platform on fear, anxiety,

00:47:38.080 --> 00:47:41.083
untruths, shall we call them, if not lies.

00:47:41.960 --> 00:47:46.960
Do you see this as a more
precarious environment

00:47:47.480 --> 00:47:50.170
as things evolve in this direction

00:47:50.170 --> 00:47:52.650
in terms of the battles you're fighting?

00:47:52.650 --> 00:47:54.080
Well, just as a citizen,

00:47:54.080 --> 00:47:56.913
I'm very concerned with
these kinds of pressures.

00:47:58.343 --> 00:48:00.460
It is something that I
think all citizens ought

00:48:00.460 --> 00:48:01.610
to be concerned about.

00:48:01.610 --> 00:48:04.520
In terms specifically of the
creation and evolution issue

00:48:04.520 --> 00:48:08.430
I think it's less closely related

00:48:08.430 --> 00:48:12.360
simply because of the
grassroots orientation

00:48:12.360 --> 00:48:15.510
and the fact that it is
not a constant thing.

00:48:15.510 --> 00:48:18.750
Where you find controversies arising

00:48:18.750 --> 00:48:22.990
over the teaching of
evolution occur at intervals,

00:48:22.990 --> 00:48:25.630
every six or seven or however many years

00:48:25.630 --> 00:48:27.970
in a given state or district.

00:48:27.970 --> 00:48:30.070
The science curriculum will be examined

00:48:30.070 --> 00:48:31.990
and the next year they'll
look at the math curriculum

00:48:31.990 --> 00:48:33.210
and the year after that they'll look

00:48:33.210 --> 00:48:34.870
at the English language arts,

00:48:34.870 --> 00:48:38.270
but at regular five to
seven years, generally,

00:48:38.270 --> 00:48:40.920
they'll take a look at
the science curriculum

00:48:40.920 --> 00:48:44.100
and that's when
anti-evolutionism may appear.

00:48:44.100 --> 00:48:46.580
Right now as we're talking,

00:48:46.580 --> 00:48:48.500
there's a problem in the state of Arizona

00:48:48.500 --> 00:48:51.110
over the adoption of
state evolution standards

00:48:51.110 --> 00:48:56.110
where the Board of Education
has tinkered around

00:48:57.140 --> 00:49:00.970
with the coverage of
climate change and evolution

00:49:00.970 --> 00:49:02.360
in a way that is not good,

00:49:02.360 --> 00:49:05.333
and so citizens are
pushing back against that.

00:49:06.220 --> 00:49:09.140
But you talked about anxieties.

00:49:09.140 --> 00:49:12.283
I think there are anxieties
that people have but they're,

00:49:14.760 --> 00:49:16.730
fascism functions much better

00:49:16.730 --> 00:49:18.870
the more diffused the anxieties are.

00:49:18.870 --> 00:49:21.720
If you are very precise
about your anxieties,

00:49:21.720 --> 00:49:23.030
you can be disproved,

00:49:23.030 --> 00:49:26.160
so it's always better to have
just sort of a general haze

00:49:26.160 --> 00:49:29.110
of anxiety out there and
you're gonna be more successful

00:49:29.110 --> 00:49:34.110
at imposing your undemocratic views.

00:49:34.680 --> 00:49:36.990
I don't think the creationism issue

00:49:36.990 --> 00:49:39.140
fits into that quite as well.

00:49:39.140 --> 00:49:44.140
It may be a secondary component
if there is an upsurge

00:49:45.310 --> 00:49:50.310
of more conservative
forms of Christianity,

00:49:50.490 --> 00:49:53.500
but conservative Christianity
is not monolithic

00:49:57.052 --> 00:49:59.880
in terms of the kinds of political views

00:49:59.880 --> 00:50:02.030
that you were talking about.

00:50:02.030 --> 00:50:06.060
There are quite a few green Christians,

00:50:06.060 --> 00:50:07.820
environmentally-oriented Christians

00:50:07.820 --> 00:50:10.290
who really believe in stewardship theology

00:50:10.290 --> 00:50:13.860
and it's their job to
reduce the amount of carbon.

00:50:13.860 --> 00:50:15.540
Climate change is a big problem.

00:50:15.540 --> 00:50:17.580
We have to do this, that, and the other.

00:50:17.580 --> 00:50:19.750
There are a lot of
social justice Christians

00:50:19.750 --> 00:50:22.320
who are very concerned about
things like immigration

00:50:22.320 --> 00:50:24.450
because we are our brother's keeper.

00:50:24.450 --> 00:50:27.910
They have biblical and
theological reasons for

00:50:31.030 --> 00:50:35.230
resisting some of the
anti-immigration statutes

00:50:35.230 --> 00:50:38.440
and so forth that may be on the way.

00:50:38.440 --> 00:50:42.950
So even if conservative
religious views are

00:50:45.310 --> 00:50:50.310
encouraged by those who
are perhaps not reflecting

00:50:51.180 --> 00:50:54.458
what I would consider
the best American values,

00:50:54.458 --> 00:50:58.300
it doesn't mean that that is
going to necessarily result

00:50:58.300 --> 00:51:01.105
in an increase in anti-evolutionism

00:51:01.105 --> 00:51:01.938
which is a long-winded answer

00:51:01.938 --> 00:51:03.180
to your question.
- But in a way

00:51:03.180 --> 00:51:05.840
you're suggesting that it's not inevitable

00:51:05.840 --> 00:51:09.470
that there's a spillover
from the evolution debate

00:51:09.470 --> 00:51:11.290
to the climate change debate.

00:51:11.290 --> 00:51:13.910
In other words, they're different actors

00:51:13.910 --> 00:51:18.910
but the one variable here is inequality,

00:51:19.010 --> 00:51:23.550
economic inequality, and
the funding of opposition,

00:51:23.550 --> 00:51:26.650
for example, to climate change.

00:51:26.650 --> 00:51:28.610
Is that something we need to worry about

00:51:28.610 --> 00:51:31.670
or is it really a strategy,

00:51:31.670 --> 00:51:33.080
what you need is a strategy

00:51:33.080 --> 00:51:38.080
of not lumping these
things together if you--

00:51:38.690 --> 00:51:40.530
- I think they're independent enough.

00:51:40.530 --> 00:51:44.620
There's a small overlap but it's focusing

00:51:44.620 --> 00:51:46.060
on that smallish overlap

00:51:46.060 --> 00:51:49.020
is probably not gonna be
the best use of resources.

00:51:49.020 --> 00:51:52.690
- Even though climate change deniers

00:51:52.690 --> 00:51:56.870
are anti-science in a way?

00:51:56.870 --> 00:51:59.750
- I don't think that they
would consider themselves that.

00:51:59.750 --> 00:52:00.610
- [Harry] I see.

00:52:00.610 --> 00:52:03.133
- I think that the people who'd, okay,

00:52:03.133 --> 00:52:05.830
they're not anti-science generically.

00:52:05.830 --> 00:52:09.060
They may be anti the
research done in this field

00:52:09.060 --> 00:52:12.120
and I've been talking to scientists

00:52:12.120 --> 00:52:14.160
on campus the last couple
of days during my visit

00:52:14.160 --> 00:52:17.110
which is always a very pleasant
part of a visit like this

00:52:17.110 --> 00:52:20.040
and I was talking to one professor.

00:52:20.040 --> 00:52:22.153
He was saying, well, you know,

00:52:22.153 --> 00:52:26.530
the evolution issue is
much more straightforward

00:52:26.530 --> 00:52:28.140
than the climate change issue

00:52:28.140 --> 00:52:31.150
in that evolution has just been so

00:52:33.000 --> 00:52:34.460
strongly established.

00:52:34.460 --> 00:52:36.120
Living things have common ancestors.

00:52:36.120 --> 00:52:38.790
That is the only explanation
that explains biology

00:52:38.790 --> 00:52:40.630
as we know it today, and we know a lot

00:52:40.630 --> 00:52:42.920
about the mechanisms and
genetics and so forth.

00:52:42.920 --> 00:52:45.110
With climate change, there are some things

00:52:45.110 --> 00:52:46.850
that we are absolutely positive about.

00:52:46.850 --> 00:52:50.510
There are core ideas of
climate change as well.

00:52:50.510 --> 00:52:53.640
CO2 and methane are warming
gases, we know that.

00:52:53.640 --> 00:52:55.760
We know that they have increased.

00:52:55.760 --> 00:52:59.290
The inference is very
clear that the increase

00:52:59.290 --> 00:53:01.480
in warming gases has
increased the temperature

00:53:01.480 --> 00:53:04.890
of the planet very rapidly
over this short period of time.

00:53:04.890 --> 00:53:09.730
Modeling is something that is
extraordinarily complicated

00:53:09.730 --> 00:53:12.620
and that scientists will disagree on,

00:53:12.620 --> 00:53:15.470
and scientific disagreement

00:53:15.470 --> 00:53:17.450
is the bread and butter of science.

00:53:17.450 --> 00:53:18.960
There's nothing wrong with that,

00:53:18.960 --> 00:53:20.790
and scientists will sometimes

00:53:20.790 --> 00:53:23.270
have exceedingly vigorous conversations

00:53:23.270 --> 00:53:25.060
and arguments about who's right,

00:53:25.060 --> 00:53:29.900
and eventually a consensus
is going to emerge

00:53:29.900 --> 00:53:33.470
but when you're saying this model shows

00:53:33.470 --> 00:53:38.310
that in 15 years the ocean is
going to be raised three feet

00:53:38.310 --> 00:53:39.810
and somebody else says, okay,

00:53:39.810 --> 00:53:42.420
but your model is wrong in
here, here, and here and here,

00:53:42.420 --> 00:53:46.193
and my model shows that the
ocean will be up six feet.

00:53:48.210 --> 00:53:51.450
That is likely a legitimate
scientific controversy.

00:53:51.450 --> 00:53:55.100
For we laymen, in terms of the
climate change controversy,

00:53:55.100 --> 00:53:57.380
the important thing is, dang,

00:53:57.380 --> 00:53:59.500
the ocean's really gonna be raising a lot.

00:53:59.500 --> 00:54:01.510
We gotta do something about this.

00:54:01.510 --> 00:54:03.270
Splitting hairs over
whether it's three feet

00:54:03.270 --> 00:54:06.580
or six feet may not be the
big worry we should have,

00:54:06.580 --> 00:54:08.370
but people who are against the idea

00:54:08.370 --> 00:54:10.980
of anthropogenic climate change

00:54:10.980 --> 00:54:13.300
are usually attacking that kind of thing

00:54:13.300 --> 00:54:18.220
rather than the basic
physics behind warming gases

00:54:18.220 --> 00:54:20.150
and their effect on the planet.

00:54:20.150 --> 00:54:23.430
- Well, Eugenie, I wanna
thank you very much

00:54:23.430 --> 00:54:26.350
for coming to Berkeley
as the Hitchcock Lecture

00:54:26.350 --> 00:54:30.190
and taking time in that
visit to be on our program

00:54:30.190 --> 00:54:32.880
and I would like to show your book again,

00:54:32.880 --> 00:54:36.550
Evolution Versus Creationism,

00:54:36.550 --> 00:54:40.220
and it's quite a good
read for somebody wanting

00:54:42.260 --> 00:54:45.200
to learn more about that debate

00:54:45.200 --> 00:54:47.900
which you've played
such an active part in.

00:54:47.900 --> 00:54:50.030
Thank you very much
for being here with us,

00:54:50.030 --> 00:54:51.350
thank you.
